## Background and Motivation

We have shipped Microsoft.Extensions.Validation in .NET 10 with experimental APIs. In .NET 11, we are making these APIs stable. In the past previews of .NET 11, we have already made and approved some API changes. This proposal only lists the new changes and the final shape for the complete API surface of the package.

We will be dropping lots of the public APIs in favor of generating them as file classes via the source generator. This gives us the most flexibility to make any changes in those APIs.

We are going to still be shipping the necessary interfaces for users to be able to plug custom implementations (e.g, non-DataAnnotations implementations)

Few notes:

- We are dropping the event because it's not really needed for Blazor, it's adding complexity to the implementation, and will make it harder (if possible at all) to keep the classes source-generated.
- We are changing the ValidationErrors dictionary to include the `ValidationError`. This includes all the info that Blazor needs and is how we are able to delete the OnValidationError event.

